#X text 15 48 converb~ is an external that generates convolution reverb for a given mono source signal. The algorithm for this is efficient enough for real-time use \, and delay time is directly proportional to the length of the impulse response.;
#X text 15 116 The basic usage of this external is given below., f 60;
#X text 458 384 Technical notes:;
#X text 458 405 * This external uses the FFTW library to generate and multiply DFTs. This is the same library used in the rfft~ internal., f 59;
#X text 458 454 * The convolution used in this external is *not* partitioned. That means that the delay is only reliant on the length of the IR \, and cannot be specified by the user. (This could be a possible improvement for future iterations of the external.);
#X text 458 530 * For the DFTs \, the flag FFTW_ESTIMATE was used. This produces DFTs that are less accurate for the sake of improved performance., f 59;
